        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-09 03:14:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-2\n\nI think this is a problem... Music API for Conductor is our responsibility, so we should review this properly. I also suggest adding a few reviewers to code commits. Otherwise, it can potentially get very problematic.\n\nPlease fix this ASAP.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "88ee6361c65539d379f346a690bc3c941f44e5f9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2197,
          "name": "Sastry Isukapalli",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sastry@research.att.com",
          "username": "sisukapalli"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-09 03:17:57.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAdding Bharath... \n\nBharath, this was my concern with pulling MUSIC code into OOF and things potentially falling through the cracks. Since it is \"MUSIC API\", someone may mistakenly assume that this code is tested in MUSIC. However, this is HAS specific code, so it should be tested. Please advise.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "046960994529bb2c593abf21381e94de5a17b0ef",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2197,
          "name": "Sastry Isukapalli",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sastry@research.att.com",
          "username": "sisukapalli"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-09 03:21:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nDileep, if reservation/service.py is not supported in R2, I think it should still have unit tests (unit tests are independent of the context the module is used).\n\nIf you will not be able to write unit tests for it, I suggest removing it from ONAP branch (e.g. move it to another folder like test).",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "88dcbfc0330e15d71891d3d4fe11beaffa35132d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3165,
          "name": "Bharath Balasubramanian",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bharathb@research.att.com",
          "username": "bharathb"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-09 03:58:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "a1f92464bd117459f199c2011bb12e1c6099cf93",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2041,
          "name": "Shankaranarayanan Puzhavakath Narayanan",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "snarayanan@research.att.com",
          "username": "snarayanan"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-09 05:01:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\ncommon/music/api.py: 407 \n\nI think the pragma is added the MockMusicAPI that is meant to be just an emulator for music and is used by Conductor. IMHO, this is okay to be not covered under unit tests.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "c9a8fe33db527282ecb13e512909a5481f6891de",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2041,
          "name": "Shankaranarayanan Puzhavakath Narayanan",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "snarayanan@research.att.com",
          "username": "snarayanan"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-09 05:05:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nFixing typos in my previous comment: \n\nI think the pragma is added to the MockMusicAPI that is meant to be just an emulator for music and is NOT used by Conductor. IMHO, this is okay to be not covered under unit tests.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "231800a123c02e2eb1f95440ee66a4075cb1ac59",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2197,
          "name": "Sastry Isukapalli",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sastry@research.att.com",
          "username": "sisukapalli"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-09 06:15:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nItem 1: conductor/conductor/common/music/voting.py\n==================================================\nThis has only two methods:\n\ndef current_time_millis():\n    \"\"\"Current time in milliseconds.\"\"\"\n    return int(round(time.time() * 1000))\n\n\ndef main(): # pragma: no cover\n[67 lines]\n\nThis has items such as:\n   # Candidate data\n    data = {\n        'Joe': 5,\n        'Shankar': 7,\n        'Gueyoung': 8,\n        'Matti': 2,\n        'Kaustubh': 0\n    }\n\nLooking at it, it seems to be more close to a unit test for MUSIC than conductor core code.\nI think it should move to a test folder at a minimum...\n\n\nItem 2: conductor/conductor/controller/service.py\n=================================================\n\nLine 72: class ControllerServiceLauncher(object): # pragma: no cover\n  + 35 lines of code that seem to launch the service\n\nthis seems an important component, so a \"no cover\" appears to be out of place.\n\n\nItem 3: conductor/conductor/common/music/messaging/component.py\n===============================================================\nclass RPCService(cotyledon.Service): # pragma: no cover\n[+ 248 lines in the class]\n\nIt is quite a bit of code in one \"no cover\"\n\nItem 4: conductor/conductor/common/music/api.py\n===============================================\nLine 407: class MockAPI(object):  # pragma: no cover\n[+ 118 lines in the class]\n\nThis class should ideally be refactored into a test folder.\n\nThere are a few others, but are in the same general direction:\ntest code inside main modules and that is not covered by test cases can be risky.\nFurther, if the persons writing the unit tests are not original authors of the code,\nextra caution is warranted so that things don't slip through the cracks.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "cff141894037877a3d0b1e8dfedc618ce9c3cf4f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1883,
          "name": "ramki krishnan",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ramkri123@gmail.com",
          "username": "ramkri123"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-09 07:34:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nConcur with Sastry.\n\nWe should add appropriate comments in the code to clearly indicate if is a unit test or not and move to test directory or remove pragma as appropriate.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
